    • Method Detail

      • buildingIdentifier

        public LocationRequest.Builder buildingIdentifier(String buildingIdentifier)
        Set the building identifier of the building where you will start positioning. If this value is not set the positioning will start in indoor-outdoor mode.

      • interval

        public LocationRequest.Builder interval(int interval)
        Set the interval in which the locations will be send to the server (in milliseconds) in Cloud mode. This value will be rounded to an integer second In Inphone mode the locations will be computed every second. Default value is 1000

      • indoorProvider

        public LocationRequest.Builder indoorProvider(LocationRequest.IndoorProvider indoorProvider)
        Set the indoor location provider. Default value is LocationRequest.IndoorProvider.HYBRID

      • useBle

        public LocationRequest.Builder useBle(boolean useBle)
        Set if you want to use BLE for positioning. Default value is true

      • useWifi

        public LocationRequest.Builder useWifi(boolean useWifi)
        Set if you want to use Wifi for positioning. Default value is true

      • motionMode

        public LocationRequest.Builder motionMode(LocationRequest.MotionMode motionMode)
        (EXPERIMENTAL) Set the motion mode. Default value is LocationRequest.MotionMode.BY_FOOT

      • useForegroundService

        public LocationRequest.Builder useForegroundService(boolean useForegroundService)
        (EXPERIMENTAL) Run the service in foreground. By default services are background, meaning that if the system needs to kill them to reclaim more memory they can be killed without too much harm. You can set this option to avoid this. A notification will be shown to the user while is running. You can set this notification with LocationRequest.setForegroundServiceNotification(Notification)
        Parameters:
        useForegroundService - true to run the service in foreground, false otherwise

      • foregroundServiceNotification

        public LocationRequest.Builder foregroundServiceNotification(android.app.Notification foregroundServiceNotification)
        Set the notification used if the service is running in foreground. Used only if LocationRequest.setUseForegroundService(Boolean) is true
        Parameters:
        foregroundServiceNotification - the notification to use running in foreground

      • outdoorLocationOptions

        public LocationRequest.Builder outdoorLocationOptions(OutdoorLocationOptions outdoorLocationOptions)
        Set outdoor location options. Only used in an indoor/outdoor request
        Parameters:
        outdoorLocationOptions - the outdoor location options
        See Also:
        OutdoorLocationOptions
